8 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Definitions. As used in [sections 3 through 8], unless the context
9 requires otherwise, the following definitions apply:
10 (1) "Bias" means prejudice for or against a party or issue arising for reasons other than the facts of
11 a case or the law governing a case. Bias in a judge may be inferred from comments, facial expressions, prior
12 activity, distortion of the law to obtain a particular result, or a conflict of interest DISPLAYED BY USING EPITHETS,
13 SLURS, DEMEANING NICKNAMES, OR THREATENING, INTIMIDATING, OR HOSTILE ACTS OR BODY LANGUAGE THAT CREATES
14 AN APPEARANCE OF BIAS OR PREJUDICE.
