20 (5)(4) "Impartiality" means the practice of making judicial decisions in accordance with the law, fairly,
21 and without evidence of bias ABSENCE OF PREJUDICE IN FAVOR OF OR AGAINST PARTICULAR PARTIES OR CLASSES OF
22 PARTIES AS WELL AS THE MAINTENANCE OF AN OPEN MIND WHEN CONSIDERING ISSUES THAT MAY COME BEFORE A
23 JUDGE.
