25 (7)(6) "Open-mindedness" means a willingness to:
26 (a) consider opposing views and alternative solutions permitted by law for resolving cases;
27 (b) remain open to persuasion despite a judge's existing views;
28 (c) concede that there is an appearance of one's own bias; and
